Everyone's going back into routine again, crazy to say for most after 6 months of been in lockdown. Brains have literally switched off. 
Quick reminder to benefit all: 
Punctuality is an important trait for an effective Islamic living. Being punctual will earn a person credibility and respect and build a positive reputation for his or her character.
Punctuality paves the way for a peaceful and tranquil productive Islamic living; it will make you feel content and happy rather than frustrated and guilty. Being early for meetings or other events, gives you time to relax, plan and prioritize the activities to bring success.

When asked our beloved Prophet (ﷺ), which act is the best?
He ( ﷺ) said: AsSalat at their fixed times, being dutiful to parents... 

Above Hadith has given great significance for being punctual, dutiful and striving, all of which are vital traits of a true believer.
