Assalamu Alaikum wa Rahmatullahi wa Barakatuh to the one reading this.

Become a better Muslim. In order to be a true Muslim (one who has to be completely submitted to the will of Allah) a person has to put Islam into practice and follow the guidance religiously. We have to be steadfast and humble. This is a reminder for myself and for us all to make constant Dhikr (remembrance of Allah).
.
.
.
May Allah guide us all on to the right path and make us, our family and loved ones among the people of Paradise. May Allah (SWT) make us one of His righteousness and greatful servants. May He save us and protect us from the trials of life and death, from the punishment of the grave and from the punishment of the hell fire and from His hatred and wrath. May He happily forgive us and have mercy on us always. May He give us both goodness in this world and in the Hereafter. May Allah grant us Jannat ul Firdaus, may He grant us Jannat u Firdaus, May He grant us Jannat ul Firdaus. And make us the first to enter Paradise with Prophet Muhammad (peace and blessing of Allah be upon him)
Ameen. .
